items.text:
Guten Abend zusammen,

ich würde gerne zwei Workshop-Angebote mit Euch teilen, die wirklich absolut klasse sind:

Zum einen veranstalten wir -nach unserem ausgebuchten Termin im November 2025 in Berlin- einen weiteren STUNT-WORKSHOP (mit Stuntprofi Tanja de Wendt) im MÄRZ 2026 in KÖLN. Es sind keine Vorerfahrungen notwendig und wir heißen alle Fitnesslevels herzlich Willkommen!

Zum anderen veranstalten wir am 17. FEBRUAR 2026 im Rahmen der BERLINALE 2026 einen LIVE-CASTING-WORKSHOP (mit Casting Director Tanja Schuh & Regisseur Christian Werner). Dieser Workshop wird ausschließlich für professionelle Schauspieler*innen und Nachwuchstalente zugänglich sein.

Alle Informationen & ANMELDUNG über unsere Website: https://www.agentur-engelspost.de/workshops-coachings/workshops-und-weiterbildungen/

...oder per Mail an: info@agentur-engelspost.com!

Workshop-Interessierte dürfen sich ebenfalls gerne per Mail melden. Dann nehme ich Euch gerne in unseren Workshop-Newsletter auf.

Happy Weekend.

GVL-förderbar KOSTEN: *480 € Early-Bird (bis 15.02.2026): *430 € Nur 12 Plätze *Alle Preise verstehen sich zzgl. 19% MwSt. Ratenzahlung auf Anfrage! INFOS & ANMELDUNG unter: www.agentur-engelspost.de'

items.text:
Hallo an alle!

Wir drehen unseren zweiten Kurzfilm “Cry Sam” und suchen hierfür den passenden Cast.

Insgesamt zu vergeben sind 5 Rollen, davon 

1 weibliche Hauptrolle
3 männliche Hauptrollen sowie
1 männliche Nebenrolle.

Die genauen Rollenbeschreibungen, sowie weitere Infos zu unserem Projekt findet ihr im angehängten PDF.

Voraussichtlicher Drehzeitraum ist Herbst 2026.
Drehort ist der Neckar-Odenwaldkreis.

Es handelt sich um ein No-Budget-Projekt, Verpflegung am Set ist vorhanden, leider können wir keine Fahrtkosten und Unterkunft zahlen.

Meldet euch gerne direkt per Nachricht oder auch per Mail an katlenafilm@gmail.com

**Anna McAuley Casting is looking for real** **North West-based families and couples for an** **exciting commercial for Chester Zoo.**

**Filming:** 10th February 2026

No acting experience required but participants should be comfortable on camera. Paid opportunity.

Apply via email or Jotform: [https://eu.jotform.com/form/260193491371356](https://eu.jotform.com/form/260193491371356)

Adult BSF: £350 / Buyout: £500

items.text:
Casting for leading Man/Leading Lady young adult early to mid-20's.
I'm shooting another short vertical demo for two days between now and February 8 (dates TBA) and am looking for two non-union actors with comedic acting chops, to play out the dialogue in this romantic comedy (a few scenes).

Shooting will be in downtown and East Vancouver, there will be a rehearsal day after actors are off-book and then we shoot.

This is a demo, voluntary, for actors reel and directing sample.

If interested, please email me your photo, resume and availability to castingproject604@gmail.com.

items.text:
**CASTING CALL - Non-union **

Looking for Slavic/Eastern European looking actors for small, non-speaking roles in short film, During Winter, I Thought of My Father, a Russian language short film by Daniil Vasilyev. 

**ACTORS DO NOT NEED TO SPEAK RUSSIAN AS THE ROLES ARE NON-SPEAKING. **

**Main Shoot Dates: Feb 14th-16th, 2026 **

**Descriptions: **

**Young Russian Man, early 20s: **Need him available for a day in the week leading up to Feb 14th for a photoshoot. 
Specific date TBD, but we are flexible and willing to work with actor's schedule. 

**Older Russian Woman, 50s-60s: **Needed for photoshoot Feb 16th. 

**Older Russian Man, 40s-60s: **Needed for filming Feb 14th, 15th, photoshoot on the 16th. Non-speaking role, will be playing main character's father. 

**Compensation: **IMDb credit, post-film credit, food provided as well as transport if required**. **

**Location: **Greater Vancouver Area 

**If interested, please send an email to ****duringwinter26@gmail.com ****with any headshots or good pictures of yourself, your reel (if you have one), and stats (height, eye colour, etc). **

** **

items.text:
🎬 CASTING – KRAKÓW | MODELE / AKTORZY / ARTYŚCI 

W związku z otwarciem nowego studia zdjęciowo-filmowego w Krakowie zapraszamy na otwarty casting do naszej bazy twarzy i talentów.

📅 Terminy: 31 stycznia (sobota) oraz 1 lutego (niedziela)
⏰ Godziny: 10:00–20:00
📍 Lokalizacja: Kraków, ul. Rękawka 10/2
💰 Udział w castingu jest BEZPŁATNY (dla chętnych w cenie 50 zł możesz otrzymać wykonane zdjęcia/ nagranie dla własnego użytku)

👤 Kogo szukamy?

 – modeli i modelek
 – aktorów i aktorek
 – statystów
 – artystów, performerów, twórców
 – osób początkujących i z doświadczeniem

📸 Dlaczego warto dołączyć do naszej bazy?

 ✔ osoby zapisane w bazie będą w pierwszej kolejności informowane o planowanych projektach (sesje, filmy, reklamy, teledyski, eventy),
 ✔ stała zniżka -20% na wynajem studia pod własne projekty i wydarzenia,
 ✔ przy większych realizacjach pomagamy w pozyskiwaniu dofinansowań na projekty artystyczne i filmowe,
 ✔ współpraca długofalowa – nie jednorazowy casting.

📋 Jak wygląda casting?

 – krótkie zdjęcia testowe (naturalne, bez stylizacji)
 – szybka rejestracja do bazy
 – przyjazna i profesjonalna atmosfera

📩 Zapisy:
https://forms.gle/gKKGP8sJzkPHsVS27

Jeśli chcesz rozwijać się w branży foto-filmowej i być częścią nowych projektów tworzonych w Krakowie - zapraszamy!

Dzień dobry, 
Szanowni Państwo,
nazywam się Ewelina Ziółkowska, jestem studentką psychologii.
Prowadzę badania do mojej pracy magisterskiej. 
Zwracam się z prośbą o udział w badaniu psychologicznym, niezbędnym dla mojej pracy
dyplomowej. 
Celem badania jest określenie zależności pomiędzy wybranymi aspektami funkcjonowania
psychospołecznego osób wykonujących zawód aktora/aktorki.
Wyniki będą wykorzystane jedynie do analizy statystycznej
Badania są anonimowe. Państwa udział w badaniu jest dobrowolny i w dowolnym
momencie można się z niego wycofać. Wyniki będą analizowane na poziomie grupowym. 
Ankieta przeznaczona jest wyłącznie dla osób wykonujących zawód aktora/aktorki.
Czas badania 10 min .
Dziękuję za poświęcony czas oraz zaangażowanie.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdswGYTR67ddhBbxScMCVQOqZMcld0zKN4FrXTBPcaaJ0x-3g/viewform

items.text:
Talent is common.

Consistency isn’t.

The actors who move forward aren’t always the most gifted…
they’re the ones who show up on the days they don’t feel like it.

The tired days.
The doubtful days.
The “what’s the point?” days.

That’s where careers are built.

Not in big moments — in small, repeated actions.

Show up. Train. Improve. Repeat.

🎭 Start here: linktr.ee/mattzina

#ConsistencyWins
#ActorMindset
#SelfMadeActor
#ActingCareer
#ActorsLife

items.text:
**CASTING CALL**

*Lead Roles for Interactive Game + Vertical Drama Production*

**Project: **The Fame Game 2: L.A. Heartbreaker

**Production: **Snail Games / Interactive Films

**Location: **Los Angeles, CA

**Shoot Dates: **March 2026 (approx. 20 days)

**Rate: **$500–$800/day

**ABOUT THE PROJECT**

This is an interactive video game production combining romance, comedy, and drama with multiple branching storylines and endings. The project involves extensive ensemble work, romantic/comedic chemistry across multiple pairings, and emotionally complex character arcs. Open to all ethnicities except where noted. Acting experience is not required, and active social media presence is a plus.

**AUDITION PROCESS**

**Round 1: **Virtual Interview (unpaid)

**Round 2: **In-person audition in Los Angeles ($100/30 min, paid) or self-tape if unable to travel

**Talent invited to round 2 must:**
* Participate in an online voting campaign
* Sign release and waiver allowing use of audition materials for voting and promotional purposes

**MIA — Female Lead**

Age: 23 | Ethnicity: Open

Gentle and competent mentor with a cool, wild streak. Professional exterior that gradually reveals a shy, jealous romantic side through interactions with the male lead.

**Requirements:**
* Sophisticated demeanor; ability to convey subtle emotional shifts
* Stunt/action experience a plus (driving scenes)

**CAMILLE — Female Lead**

Age: 24 | Ethnicity: Open

A confident, bold print model who plays games with love but transforms into someone capable of genuine emotion. Sexy, fiery, and provocative, but ultimately vulnerable.

**Requirements:**
* Model experience a plus
* Comfortable with flirtatious/sensual scenes
* Strong emotional range

**LIN MUYUN — Female Lead**

Age: 27 | Ethnicity: Mixed / Half Asian

Gentle and elegant on the surface, highly possessive underneath. Carries childhood trauma and develops complicated feelings for her stepbrother. Borderline obsessive but deeply sympathetic.

**Requirements:**
* Comfortable with intimate/intense emotional scenes
* Ability to portray psychological complexity

**ROLES**
**SHUHAN HO — Male Lead**

Age: 23 | Ethnicity: Chinese / East Asian

An ordinary international student mistaken for a wealthy heir with an identical appearance. Vain and drawn to glamour, but kind-hearted beneath the surface. Awkward yet sincere, constantly juggling multiple romantic entanglements while navigating his double identity.

**Requirements:**
* Strong comedic timing; ability to portray vulnerability and growth
* Chemistry with multiple female leads
* Must play two characters (Shuhan Ho and Shuhan “Richie” Ho)
* Mandarin Chinese fluency required

**SHUHAN “RICHIE” HO — Male Supporting**

Age: 23 | Ethnicity: Chinese / East Asian

The true rich heir—and a complete emotional predator. Hedonistic, selfish, and unapologetically cruel in matters of love. Free of guilt or conscience, he is the protagonist's dark mirror and the original source of the story's turmoil.

**Requirements: **Same as Shuhan Ho (dual role)

**SUSANNA — Female Lead**

Age: 21 | Ethnicity: East Asian

A pampered rich heiress, innocent and stubborn, completely clueless about everyday life. Outwardly confident but inwardly fragile and insecure. Clumsy yet endearing in her attempts to win love.

**Requirements:**
* Ability to balance comedy with emotional vulnerability
* Physical comedy skills preferred
* Must deliver Chinese, Japanese, or Korean dialogue with authentic/native pronunciation (fluency not required)

**LI SISI — Female Lead**

Age: 22 | Ethnicity: Chinese / East Asian

Pure, kind, girl-next-door type. The male lead's moral compass and childhood sweetheart. Sweet but capable of jealousy and testing born from insecurity.

**Requirements:**
* Natural, understated performance style
* Chemistry with male lead; ability to convey heartbreak
* Must deliver Chinese dialogue with authentic/native pronunciation

**TO SUBMIT**
1. Headshot and full-body photo
2. Acting resume

**Send submissions to: **casting@rarefloweragency.com

**Deadline: Feb 8, 2026 (12PM, PST)**

علط عسري 
Lo que para nosotros son estilos musicales para los Iraquies se reduce a estilos de canto, cada estilo de canto aporta la esencia y alma de la construcción musical. Es decir, puedo tener alguno de los ritmos populares dentro de la construcción músical, pero quien le dan personalidad y por consecuencia el formato musical que posteriormente tendrá su respectivo nombre es el estilo de canto que la compone! 

Es por esto que muchas veces encontramos en canciones Iraquies ritmos populares, que para nosotr@s determinan un estilo de danza, peroooo, no siempre es así, ya que podemos podemos encontrar en ciertos estilos folclóricos como por ej, el Chobi, donde encontramos su ritmo característico propio de este estilo, y aún así encontrar algún otro ritmo popular de otros estilos. 

Te gustaría saber más sobre estilos de danza, canto, ritmos Iraquies!? 
Adentrate a este fascinante mundo en mi formación Online! 
Encontrarás distintos cursos que se adapten a tu necesidad!

🇮🇶 Formación profesional de danzas Iraquies
🇮🇶 Especialización Iraqi folk
🇮🇶 Intensivo Iraqi dance
🇮🇶 Trainning
🇮🇶 Coreografía 
🇮🇶 Talleres para escuelas

SHOOT OPPORTUNITY; ONE DAY ONLY

M. 50’s-70’s, Sheriff Role Available for Improv Comedy Short Film.  

*Chief Harris is a small town bumbling sheriff who loves pancakes and isn't that great at his job. He's very southern, and means well. In this short film, Chief Harris is sitting down with a documentary crew to tell the story of a series of serial murders that occurred 20 years ago.*

Submit your headshot to comesaroundmovie@gmail.com to receive more info. 

Signup with our Calendly link for a virtual audition! [https://calendly.com/comesaroundmovie/30min](https://calendly.com/comesaroundmovie/30min) 

Shooting will occur in Lakeland Fl, on January 24th 2026 from 9am-4:30pm.

Talent will receive up to $25 in travel cost reimbursement.

items.text:
Hej
Jeg er ved at udvikle en crime spillefilm i København (bor selv i Esbjerg) og søger kvindelige og mandelige skuespiller af alder 20 til 28 

og statister af alder 20 til 65 der kan give en følelsesmæssig dybde til en scene med bandekonflikt.

Hvis du synes det lyder interessant, send gerne en casting klip hvor du ytre dig. Herefter kan vi tage en snak og måske mødes – så vi både kan arbejde sammen på projektet og mærke, om vi også har god menneskelig kemi.

Ser frem til at høre fra dig 🕶️🎬

Vh

Jonas Helsvig

message.text:
SONGS FROM LIFE with Stefanie Rummel  @adlfringe & @newcastlefringe Fringe 
Let the melodies carry you... the stories transform you.

AUSTRALIAN PREMIERE: 
https://adelaidefringe.com.au/fringetix/songs-from-life-af2026

Award-winning singer Stefanie Rummel takes you on a captivating musical journey — from the cafés of Paris to the cabarets of Berlin, and the clubs of Manhattan. 
Featuring songs in the style of Piaf, Weill, Sondheim, and her own original works.
Through stories and songs, Stefanie ignites longing, laughter, and love — in a show that touches hearts and minds.
Seven chansons were written by Stefanie Rummel (lyrics & music). They were arranged and produced in collaboration with Tom Schlüter (pianist & music producer).
Praised as “soul-touching” and “brilliant showmanship”, Stefanie Rummel has enchanted audiences across the US, UK, Europe, and Australia.
“You beautifully blended your life experiences and stories into a creative music journey with such thoughtful themes. Your insights and heartfelt messages truly moved me and continue to echo in my heart long after the show.”
★★★★ “Outstanding Voice”  TheReviewHub
★★★★ “Revelation”  LondonTheatre1

A sparkling celebration of life, music, and connection — cabaret at its most heartfelt.

Europe’s Award-Winning Voice:
https://youtu.be/tplyVnOjMxo

items.text:
🎸 Durch eine Einladung in Instagram, durch den Musiker und Schauspieler Florian Thunemann, bin ich gestern auf dieses kleine Kultur-Universum gestoßen: 

🕊️ „Long Erich & Friends“ trifft „Lohse Saiten“, von Blues, Rock und Folk bis Gypsy Swing. 

🤍 Ich habe Florian zwei Fotos gemacht und heute am PC daraus ein kleines Video geformt, Gitarrenmusik darunter, Herz darüber. 

🎸 Dabei ist mir dieser Vers in den Kopf gekommen und ich lasse ihn genau so stehen: 

🕊️ "So wie Du Bilder 
zu Geschichten formst, 
formt der Groove Dich 
zu einem Menschen, 
der wieder im Takt atmet." 

🤍 Livemusik ist mehr als Unterhaltung, sie ist ein friedlicher Treffpunkt für Körper, Geist und Seele. Wenn Kultur überall genug Raum bekommt, wird die Welt leiser im Hass und lauter im Verstehen, dann geben wir nicht denen Macht, die vom Krieg leben, sondern denen, die vom Miteinander erzählen. 

🤍🎸🕊️ Unterstütze Clubs, Bühnen, Straßenmusik, Proberäume, kleine Events, genau dort fängt Frieden an, im echten Klang, in echten Blicken, in echter Nähe. 

🤍🎸🕊️ Bilder und Text @christian_weisse_digi_content 

#LongErichAndFriends #LohseSaiten #FlorianThunemann #Wundertuete #Koeln

items.summary:
🎸 Durch eine Einladung in Instagram, durch den Musiker und Schauspieler Florian Thunemann, bin ich gestern auf dieses kleine Kultur-Universum gestoßen: 

🕊️ „Long Erich & Friends“ trifft „Lohse Saiten“, von Blues, Rock und Folk bis Gypsy Swing. 

🤍 Ich habe Florian zwei Fotos gemacht und heute am PC daraus ein kleines Video geformt, Gitarrenmusik darunter, Herz darüber. 

🎸 Dabei ist mir dieser Vers in den Kopf gekommen und ich lasse ihn genau so stehen: 

🕊️ "So wie Du Bilder 
zu Geschichten formst, 
formt der Groove Dich 
zu einem Menschen, 
der wieder im Takt atmet." 

🤍 Livemusik ist mehr als Unterhaltung, sie ist ein friedlicher Treffpunkt für Körper, Geist und Seele. Wenn Kultur überall genug Raum bekommt, wird die Welt leiser im Hass und lauter im Verstehen, dann geben wir nicht denen Macht, die vom Krieg leben, sondern denen, die vom Miteinander erzählen. 

🤍🎸🕊️ Unterstütze Clubs, Bühnen, Straßenmusik, Proberäume, kleine Events, genau dort fängt Frieden an, im echten Klang, in echten Blicken, in echter Nähe. 

🤍🎸🕊️ Bilder und Text @christian_weisse_digi_content 

#LongErichAndFriends #LohseSaiten #FlorianThunemann #Wundertuete #Koeln

CASTING CALL - ASAP

25/01/25

The Party No One Wanted (Short Film)

**A dark comedy about grief and family relationships.**

Robbie and Mary have to get through an excruciating memorial that has a DJ, karaoke and a pregnancy announcement / gender reveal planned by their half sister Lisa.

* **Shooting 6th - 9th March in TW19**
* Auditions in Elephant and Castle within the next few weeks
* **Travel Expenses Paid**
* Student film hoping to go to Film festivals
* **Robbie **(28-38yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Emotionally withdrawn but has a kind heart, he's holding it together for Mary and his Dad
* **Steve** (57-70yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Mary, Robbie and Lisa’s dad doesn’t get involved in the arguing he’s still devastated by the loss of his wife but insists he’s fine.
* **Lisa** (39-47yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Self centred and definitely doesn’t know whats appropriate at a memorial. 
* **Natalie** (49-65yrs)
   * A close family friend who has taken on a bit of a motherly role to everyone, kind and soft spoken.
* **Bill** (50-65yrs) 
   * The drunk best friend of steve who has awful timing for his awkward comments. Very funny character

**Character Bios: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing)** **

**Director’s Statement: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing) 

Email: [mhmollie0303@icloud.com](mailto:mhmollie0303@icloud.com) for further details

items.text:
CASTING CALL – LIVERPOOL ACTORS WANTED 

We're casting for "They Were All Some Mothers' Sons" – a powerful true story returning to the stage at Shakespeare North Playhouse, Prescot in May 2026.

This sell-out production tells the remarkable true story of German POWs detained in Huyton during WWII who fell in love with local women and chose to stay, becoming part of our community. 

Previously performed to packed houses in Liverpool and Germany.

Roles available:

 Jean – female, playing age 18-25

 Eleanor – female, playing age 18-25

 Marjorie – female, playing age 18-25

 Joey – Young British RAF pilot, male, playing age 18-24

 Mother – female, playing age 40+

 Father – male, playing age 40+

Key dates:

 Auditions: First week of February

 Rehearsals: Mid-March to show

 Performances: 1st, 2nd May 2026 (possible 3rd date)

 Venue: Shakespeare North Playhouse, Prescot

This is a paid role (profit share)

This is Prescot's own heritage story—told in the heart of Knowsley, where it all happened over 80 years ago. We're looking for passionate local talent to bring this living history to life.

To apply: Send your CV and headshot to howl.michael1963@yahoo.co.uk specifying which role and which production you want to audition for.

Please prepare a 2-minute monologue of your choice for audition.

Actors Wanted!  - Feb 2nd

We are casting for a short comedy commercial as part of our final year for UWE Bristol Filmmaking BA course. 

This is a student production, seeking voluntary actors. The film is non-commercial and will be used for portfolio and university showcase.

Bristol-based, evening shoot on Feb 2nd.

To apply, please send headshots, showreels and CVs to koby2.day@live.uwe.ac.uk

**CASTING CALL – LONDON – THEATRE – PROFIT SHARE**

We are casting for a new adaptation of **Sophocles’ *****Antigone***, scheduled for performance in **late March / April 2026** (exact dates and venue TBC).

This is an **independent production**, developed by producer and actress **Ioanna Firaku** and co-producer and director **Una Reitere**. Due to the nature of the project, this is a **low-budget, profit-share production**, with performers paid from shared ticket-sale profits. While finances are modest, we are committed to creating a focused, rigorous, and artistically ambitious production.

**ROLES AVAILABLE**

We strongly encourage performers of **all backgrounds, ethnicities, and abilities** to apply. **Gender is not a determining factor for any role**, and all characters are open to inclusive and non-traditional casting.

All roles will involve chorus work and some devising capabilities.

**CREON / CHORUS**

*A text-heavy role.*

Newly appointed ruler of Thebes. Charismatic and authoritative, Creon believes deeply in law, order, and civic responsibility. He governs with conviction and a strong sense of duty, convinced that stability must come before personal feeling.

Rather than a villain, Creon is a leader acting from **good intentions**, whose certainty is gradually tested and fractured. As the play unfolds, moments of doubt, vulnerability, and moral conflict emerge beneath his controlled exterior. The role requires an actor capable of navigating power alongside insecurity, righteousness alongside fear, and authority alongside humanity.

Strong command of language, emotional range, and stamina for dense text are essential.

**ISMENE** / **EURYDICE / CHORUS**

Ismene: Antigone’s sister. Cautious, empathetic, and pragmatic, Ismene is torn between loyalty and fear. She represents survival, compromise, and the instinct to endure rather than resist.

Willing to move on and adapt to circumstances, Ismene’s convictions are tested when her loyalty is questioned. The role requires emotional subtlety and the ability to hold inner conflict beneath restraint.

Eurydice: Creon’s partner and Queen of Thebes. Appearing in a shorter scene towards the tragic end of the play, Eurydice carries immense emotional weight. The role demands the ability to convey grief, fear, and moral clarity through restraint, quiet strength, and a deeply grounded presence.

**HAEMON / CHORUS**

Creon’s child and Antigone’s intended. Passionate, idealistic, and emotionally conflicted, Haemon stands between generations and opposing ideologies. Courageous enough to challenge authority, they refuse to remain the dutiful child, actively confronting inherited power and breaking cycles of generational trauma.

**TEIRESIAS / GUARD / MESSENGER / CHORUS**

*A text-heavy role.*

Multiple roles requiring strong storytelling ability, versatility, and clear characterisation. **Teiresias** is the truth-bearer of the play, demanding a commanding presence and a sense of wisdom beyond human years. In contrast, the **Guard** and **Messenger** ground the world of the play in realism, offering sharp tonal shifts and, at times, moments of dark or dry humour that briefly lighten the weight of the tragedy.

**REHEARSALS & PERFORMANCE**
* Rehearsals will take place over Zoom, and in London (schedule to be confirmed collaboratively).
* Performances anticipated **late March / April 2026**.
* Venue and final dates are currently being secured.
**TO APPLY**

Please email **antigone.production2026@gmail.com** with:
* The role(s) you wish to be considered for
* A headshot **or** Spotlight link / CV

Selected applicants will be sent a short self-tape audition script.

**Audition deadline:** *08.02.2026 12am*

If you have any questions, feel free to reach out via email.

Thank you,

Ioanna

29-31 January in Berlin.

In this workshop Antonia Cezara Cioază and Jakob Nielsen are sharing their personal training called IMAGINING WITH THE BODY-MIND which they have developed together with their director, Eugenio Barba since January 2022. 

The training is based on the use of imagination in the pre-expressive level of the creative process of the actor.

Through guided work in embodied presence and spontaneous exploration, participants learn to access their intuitive responses and channel them into focused, expressive action. The participants will explore composition by practising varied ways of walking and dancing. 

They can use the exercises in their personal practice order to enhance their stage presence. The exercises are crafted to let participants tap into their own associations, opening pathways to authentic expression on stage.

More details: [https://imaginingbodymind.carrd.co](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fimaginingbodymind.carrd.co%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAc3J0YwZhcHBfaWQQMjIyMDM5MTc4ODIwMDg5MgABHmwgV6ATObZ3kmmCDbESsuL7JJ8ikSuIXxovuJRvRolTYi2wK_hX9m28KHjI_aem_KXbemAkoiwLRQWeL6zJhhA&h=AT1H9OBzjQyXL6cmaONDfv0q223N8TRU6_uKZ4Av-zAritd4t408rQzHkwAUTZW17V52l6-dScMAYaAK3IADk0mHta98eae8pHcZF6NotDXMduXrRRMtM6A-fjhv27QqroYSnuopKrBSfoLQC88NnWZuHHptDA&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT3Lu1X4iM3PjxlrZwntZon8UXjvDj_OF40QYKaLurcg3zTswjbkbQ0I37wr9A_DnWB-dMmSp7Gjfv2bdzW3Hz4xBdeGCsrCaS_q8-vhY0wx-LZJ9XPS6WW6h5LFRkzxkA_7KEqO49p2eU6mrqpY3XF0Tzidw2rwKLC-HsjMOmsQYyYryoA2JDveMds)

Szukacie prezentu, który wywoła efekt WOW i nie wyląduje w szufladzie? 

Cześć! Chciałem Wam pokazać coś, co ostatnio dopracowałem. To personalizowane obrazy na płótnie, ale w wydaniu AI. Możecie zamienić zdjęcie bliskiej osoby, psa albo kota w postać z komiksu, superbohatera, czy – jak w przypadku mojej babci na zdjęciu – w raperkę w dresie! 

Najfajniejsze jest to, że nie kupujecie kota w worku:

Wchodzicie na jakchceszsklep.pl

Wgrywacie zdjęcie.

Opisujecie pomysł (np. "zrób z niego wikinga" albo "ubierz ją w dres").

AI wygeneruje Wam podgląd ZA DARMO!  Możecie się pobawić i zobaczyć efekty bez żadnych opłat.

Jeśli efekt Wam się spodoba, drukujemy to na porządnym płótnie. 

 Sprawdźcie sami: jakchceszsklep.pl
 Z kodem PREZENT10 macie -10% na całe zamówienie.

items.text:
**Szukam modelki na zasadzie TFP Gliwice/Katowice ( Śląsk ) ‘’Anioł’’**

 

Szukam pań które nie krępują się własnego ciała i chciałaby mieć ciekawą pamiątkę w postaci klimatycznych zdjęć. Wiem jak bardzo jest ważna akceptacja własnego ciała bo przez to też możemy inaczej funkcjonować. Przez takie zdjęcia można również tego dokonać. Sesja w głównej mierze jest jako taki motywator. Tematem sesji będzie sensualny Anioł.

 

Poszukuje kobiety w **wieku od 20 - 45 **lat nie koniecznie z doświadczeniem pozowania, na zasadach Tfp mieszkającej w Gliwicach lub okolicach Zabrze czy Katowice najdalej. Posiadam na wyposażeniu mini studio z kilkoma tłami oraz lampami. Mam również duży wybór kostiumów i gadżetów do wykorzystywania. Główny motyw do kobieta: Piękna i drapieżna! Sama sesja trwa przeważnie od 1,5h do 2h w zalezności od motywów.

** **

**Zapraszam na stronę**

** **

**Facebook Łukasz Magiera – Fotografia**

www.instagram.com/lukasz.magiera.official

 

Więcej informacji na Priv

items.text:
Zapraszamy do Statystowania w projekcie zapowiadającym wiosenną ramówkę

3  Luty (Wtorek) :
🎬 Góral - mężczyzna  w wieku 45-55 lat
🎬 Wędkarz - mężczyzna z brodą w wieku 40-50 lat 

4 luty (Środa) :

🎬 Pasażerowie różny wiek 
🎬 Strażacy mężczyźni w wieku 30-40
🎬 Rolnicy/mieszkancy  w wieku 40-50 lat 

❗️PROSIMY O PILNE ZGŁOSZENIA ❗️

Osoby zainteresowane prosimy o PILNE zgłoszenia na e-mail: statysci@profesjatv.pl
w temacie wpisujemy: wybrana postać/rolę np. Góral 

Wiadomość powinna zawierać:
• imię i nazwisko, wiek
• aktualne zdjęcia twarzy i sylwetki 
• telefon kontaktowy 
• wymiary (rozmiar ubrań, wzrost, pas, talia) 

Plan będzie realizowany w Warszawie 
Stawka 200zl brutto  płatne po planie

items.text:
**NOWY SERIAL DOKUMENTALNY TRUE CRIME **

**WARSZAWA **

**31.01 / 1.02 / 3.02 / 5.02 **

Do nowego serialu dokumentalnego w formule true crime poszukuję statystów oraz statystów kontynuacyjnych, głównie mężczyzn oraz kilku kobiet wg dat podanych przy konkretnych postaciach.

**Statysta kontynuacyjny 31.01, 1.02 oraz 3.02 (wnętrza):**
* **KRZYSIEK **- mężczyzna, w wieku ok. 25 lat, szczupły, wysoki brunet

**Stawka: 510zł** płatne po zakończeniu kontynuacji 

**Statyści kontynuacyjni 31.01 oraz 1.02 (wnętrza):**
* **MŁODY F.** - mężczyzna w wieku 30+, ciemne krótkie włosy, niewysoki
* **PROKURATOR** - mężczyzna w wieku 30+, wysoki blondyn, typ elegancki
* **FUNKCJONARIUSZ** - mężczyzna w wieku 30+

**Stawka: 340zł** płatne po drugim dniu zdjęciowym

**Statysta kontynuacyjny 31.01, 1.02, 3.02 oraz 5.02 (wnętrza):**

**WŁODEK** - mężczyzna, w wieku 40+, ok. 170cm wzrostu, otyły, z dużymi dłońmi, typ człowieka pracującego

**Stawka: 680zł** płatne po zakończeniu kontynuacji*

*UWAGA (!) możliwe dodatkowe 2 lub 3 dni zdjęciowe pod koniec lutego - wymagana dyspozycyjność. 

Zgłoszenia wysyłajcie na adres: **patrycja@podtytulem.pl**

W tytule: nazwa postaci + TC

W treści: imię i nazwisko, wiek, nr telefonu, miejscowość oraz ZDJĘCIE TWARZY I SYLWETKI tylko z dnia zgłoszenia + ZDJĘCIE DŁONI (dłonie zadbane, paznokcie naturalne!).

Zgłoszenia bez zdjęcia dłoni nie będą brane pod uwagę.

ZDJĘCIE TWARZY - portretowe selfie w dziennym świetle, na wprost, patrząc w obiektyw. Bez żadnych filtrów. Bez okularów. Bez nakrycia głowy. Kolorowe.

ZDJĘCIE SYLWETKI – aktualne, cała sylwetka

items.text:
CASTING CALL- LITTLE STEPS I NEVER SAW
📍The North East England📍Filming 18th-28th February 2026 🎥

* We are looking for a male in their late 40s-70 year old to play the old man in the film

* We’re a small group of passionate Student Filmmakers in our final year of Sunderland University. Looking for actors who, like us, want to get into the industry and or professional actors who want to help out the little guys. 🎬

📍The production is based in Tynemouth in the North East of England

The Film explores the deep emotions surrounding loss and the blessing of watching your child grow up in front of your eyes. ‘The Little Steps I never Saw’ is a psychological, Liminal Realism and Poetic Fantasy story that is deeply routed in symbolism and mystery.

This role will be UNPAID. However we will pay for all travel expenses 🚝 and good food will be provided on set. 🍕

⚠️Note: this film will be submitted into film festival’s 🎉

Contact: 📞

georgia.dodsworth24@gmail.com

❗️Please be prepared to provide a photo of yourself❗️📸

items.text:
Talent is common.

Consistency isn’t.

The actors who move forward aren’t always the most gifted…
they’re the ones who show up on the days they don’t feel like it.

The tired days.
The doubtful days.
The “what’s the point?” days.

That’s where careers are built.

Not in big moments — in small, repeated actions.

Show up. Train. Improve. Repeat.

🎭 Start here: linktr.ee/mattzina

#ConsistencyWins
#ActorMindset
#SelfMadeActor
#ActingCareer
#ActorsLife

Talent is common.

Consistency isn’t.

The actors who move forward aren’t always the most gifted…
they’re the ones who show up on the days they don’t feel like it.

The tired days.
The doubtful days.
The “what’s the point?” days.

That’s where careers are built.

Not in big moments — in small, repeated actions.

Show up. Train. Improve. Repeat.

🎭 Start here: linktr.ee/mattzina

#ConsistencyWins
#ActorMindset
#SelfMadeActor
#ActingCareer
#ActorsLife

Check out my latest 2026 showreels, 2026 Voiceover demo, other videos and an updated list of credits that reflect my journey over the years in the world of acting.

items.text:
🎬🎞️Casting call for student short film: ‘Don’t Forget the Butter’  

We are casting for a short film (7-9 minutes) for our second year project at Greenwich University.

Synopsis:

A man sets out to complete the next task on a bucket list: find the best toast topping. As the story unfolds, it is revealed that the bucket list belonged to his late girlfriend, who passed suddenly and unexpectedly. Completing the list becomes his way of honouring her memory and processing his grief.

Filming: East London, w/c 23rd February - w/c 2nd March (exact date TBC)

Important: Please ensure you are able to travel to East London (end of the district line) prior to expressing your interest. 

If you are interested in character 3 - you will need to be able to travel to Greenwich instead of East London, dates TBC.

As this is a student production, the roles are unpaid. However, travel and expenses and food will be provided. This film will be used within our portfolios - you are welcome to add this to your own portfolio and/or showreels. 

If you are interested or would like to hear more, please email the following to: [lh3568v@gre.ac.uk](mailto:lh3568v@gre.ac.uk) 
* Which character you are applying for
* Headshot and CV
* Availability

items.text:
🍒 **CASTING CALL: University of Westminster Graduation Short Film (LONDON)**

***CHERRY ON TOP***** — Black & surreal comedy-drama with surrealist elements**

Shooting in London between **Feb 14 – March 5** (exact dates TBC) 

5 consecutive shoot days

***Cherry on Top*** is a contained, actor-driven short film exploring emotional decay, morality, denial, and social performance through deadpan absurdity, surrealism, and escalating discomfort.

At a carefully orchestrated dinner party, two couples lose their manners as a wine-fuelled confession of infidelity exposes a far more destabilising secret. 

Throughout the film, a cooked duck on the dinner table slowly rots in plain view, completely ignored by the characters.

Performance style: **grounded, restrained, subtext-driven**. Think long silences, polite cruelty, sustained social tension.

**Catherine (Lead)**
Playing age: **30s–40s**
The dinner party hostess and Hugh’s wife. Elegant, intelligent, self-righteous, and controlling. Catherine has meticulously curated her life and believes she is emotionally evolved. As the evening unfolds, her composure slowly fractures, revealing unresolved issues and a quietly devious desperation beneath the polish.
A role requiring precision, stillness, restraint, and a slow, unsettling unravel.

**Hugh (Supporting)**
Playing age: **30s–40s**
Catherine’s husband. Timid, gentle, and emotionally reserved, Hugh avoids confrontation and retreats into routine and wine. Deeply likeable and sensitive, he is often overshadowed—until his passivity gives way to something unexpectedly dark.
Played with sincerity and understatement, allowing the absurdity to emerge naturally.

**This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Ingrid. An intimacy coordinator will be present.*

**Ingrid (LEAD)**
Playing age: **30s–40s**
Alec’s wife. Obsessive, competitive, and emotionally volatile beneath a polished exterior. Preoccupied with youth, validation, and social hierarchy—especially in comparison to Catherine. Passive-aggressive, smug, and deeply insecure.
Midway through the film, a private bathroom moment exposes her fragility as she spirals alone with her reflection.
A demanding role rooted in desperation masquerading as confidence.

**This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Hugh. An intimacy coordinator will be present.*

* This is a non-paid final-year University of Westminster production. Food and transport will be provided. Credit and showreel-quality footage guaranteed. The film may be submitted to festivals.

To apply: 

Please DM or email **cherryontop.grad.film@gmail.com **with your showreel (if available) and the role(s) you’re applying for.

Open to London-based actors or those able to self-travel.

Feel free to share and thank you! 🍒

items.text:
CASTING CALL for a Short film *RYLIE* 
A Dramatic Sci/Fi short film about a couple through Grief and the Afterlife, funded by the Toronto Arts Council. Paid. Meals included. 

Non-Union

Shooting In Mid-May in Toronto, ON, Canada.

LOGLINE: Glitches in her old footage drag a grieving woman back through the stages of loss, forcing her to confront the remnants of a relationship she can’t release and the growing gaps in her own story. 

**DAVID: SUPPORTING**

Late 20s / early 30s. Stylish but unshowy. Quiet confidence. A lived-in edge.  Creative, sensitive, observant. Carries traces of a past life: recovery, scars, depth.

Once deeply connected to RYLIE before his tragic accident. Appears both as her boyfriend and as a ghost — intimate, restrained, emotionally present rather than overtly “spooky.”

A modern romantic with a subtle punk ethos (attitude, not costume). (2 full days) $250/day

**ROOMMATE: SUPPORTING**

Early–mid 20s. Social, independent, and perpetually in motion.  juggling plans, group chats. Loves a bit of gossip and the comfort of communal chaos.

Frequently misses the quieter emotional beats in the room, not out of insensitivity but because she assumes everything will sort itself out. Brings warmth, momentum, and gentle comic relief to RYLIE’s interior world. (1 day) $250/day

**3 TRENDY FRIENDS: 2 FEATURED EXTRAS +1 BIT PART**

18 to mid 20s. all ethnicities / any genders. Three close friends, think subcultures: ravers, bandmates, skaters, goths with 2yk style. A small speaking role will be for one of the friends. Please submit separately or as a group if you can. Individual submissions will be accepted as well. Pay is based on 1 hr of shooting. $100 per person plus meal. Estimated commitment is 3-4 hours.

Please submit self-tapes via Backstage, Actors Access, or through ryliecasting@gmail.com, and please share with anyone who might be interested. thanks!

https://www.backstage.com/casting/rylie-a-scifi-drama-funded-by-tac-3072572/

This February 12th, join **AACTA & Casting Guild Award-winning casting director Anousha Zarkesh** for a rare one-day masterclass designed *for actors by a casting pro*.

👉 **Anousha Zarkesh Casting Masterclass**
📅 **Thursday, 12 February 2026**
🕙 **10 am – 4 pm**
📍 **The Audition Room, Chippendale, Sydney**
💡 Max 14 participants — intense, hands-on, and focused on YOU.

Anousha has been shaping Australian TV & film casting for **25+ years**, with credits across drama, comedy, documentary and feature film — from *Mystery Road* and *Total Control* to *Firebite* and *The Stranger*. She’s known for championing authentic performances and diverse talent.

🎤 **What you’ll get:**
• A round table discussion about *real casting practice*
• Scene work with feedback straight from a working casting director
• Insight into what casting directors are looking for *right now*
• A chance to ask the questions actors always want to ask

This isn’t about hype — it’s about meaningful craft, clarity, and confidence in the room.

https://www.thehubstudio.com.au/anousha-zarkesh-casting-masterclass/

items.text:
🎸 Durch eine Einladung in Instagram, durch den Musiker und Schauspieler Florian Thunemann, bin ich gestern auf dieses kleine Kultur-Universum gestoßen: 

🕊️ „Long Erich & Friends“ trifft „Lohse Saiten“, von Blues, Rock und Folk bis Gypsy Swing. 

🤍 Ich habe Florian zwei Fotos gemacht und heute am PC daraus ein kleines Video geformt, Gitarrenmusik darunter, Herz darüber. 

🎸 Dabei ist mir dieser Vers in den Kopf gekommen und ich lasse ihn genau so stehen: 

🕊️ "So wie Du Bilder 
zu Geschichten formst, 
formt der Groove Dich 
zu einem Menschen, 
der wieder im Takt atmet." 

🤍 Livemusik ist mehr als Unterhaltung, sie ist ein friedlicher Treffpunkt für Körper, Geist und Seele. Wenn Kultur überall genug Raum bekommt, wird die Welt leiser im Hass und lauter im Verstehen, dann geben wir nicht denen Macht, die vom Krieg leben, sondern denen, die vom Miteinander erzählen. 

🤍🎸🕊️ Unterstütze Clubs, Bühnen, Straßenmusik, Proberäume, kleine Events, genau dort fängt Frieden an, im echten Klang, in echten Blicken, in echter Nähe. 

🤍🎸🕊️ Bilder und Text @christian_weisse_digi_content 

#LongErichAndFriends #LohseSaiten #FlorianThunemann #Wundertuete #Koeln

zu einem Menschen, 
der wieder im Takt atmet." 

🤍 Livemusik ist mehr als Unterhaltung, sie ist ein friedlicher Treffpunkt für Körper, Geist und Seele. Wenn Kultur überall genug Raum bekommt, wird die Welt leiser im Hass und lauter im Verstehen, dann geben wir nicht denen Macht, die vom Krieg leben, sondern denen, die vom Miteinander erzählen. 

🤍🎸🕊️ Unterstütze Clubs, Bühnen, Straßenmusik, Proberäume, kleine Events, genau dort fängt Frieden an, im echten Klang, in echten Blicken, in echter Nähe. 

🤍🎸🕊️ Bilder und Text @christian_weisse_digi_content 

#LongErichAndFriends #LohseSaiten #FlorianThunemann #Wundertuete #Koeln

## Casting Call: Couple Talent for Lifestyle Brand Video (Squamish)

We’re casting **2 on-camera performers** to play a **couple arriving at a vacation home** for a lifestyle brand video shoot in **Squamish, BC**. 

Shoot Details
* Location: **Squamish, BC**
* Date:** Wed Feb 4th**
* Duration: **4 hours**
* Rate: **$400 flat** per person
* Union status: **Non-union**
* Usage: **Brand marketing** (web + social)

Roles (2 Talent)

**Couple (Ages 35–55)**
* Fit, active-looking individuals with an approachable, outdoorsy vibe
* Comfortable on camera with light direction
* Real couples encouraged, but not required

How to Apply

Please email the following to tom@setsail.ca:
1. **Name + age**
2. **Recent photos** (headshot + full-body; phone pics are fine)
3. **Any on-camera experience**
4. **If applying as a real couple**, include both names and photos together (optional)
5. **Availability confirmation** for the shoot window

Mogę nagrać materiały pod konkretne potrzeby, możemy razem coś wymyślić od zera, chętnie też dołączę jako +1 przy kolejnym projekcie czy wydarzeniu — jestem otwarty na różne formy współpracy.

2. Hospital: 3 people, portraying EMS personnel, dressed in scrubs, 6p-9p.

Production Company: Legacy Landmarks Studio, Golden Hour Grid

CASTING CALL - Short Dark Comedy/Noir
• Title: "Murder, No Rush"

• Type: Short

• Location: Boulder, CO, Denver, CO

• Compensation: $25/day (negotiable), lunch provided

• Shooting Dates: Sunday, January 25th & Sunday, February 1st

SYNOPSIS

Vivian, a vain housewife, conspires to kill her wealthy husband, Benny, by hiring a hitman- but unbeknownst to her, the cops know exactly what she's up to.

ROLES:

• Benny D'Angelo: Male, 23-35
Vivian's husband. A well-off businessman who fell in love easily, only to now find that his wife might have married him just for the money.

• Officer K: Male, 30+
A no-nonsense cop with a keen attention to detail. He arrives on the scene of an apparent drug bust, only to discover there may be something much more sinister at hand.
(Only needed on 1/25)

TO SUBMIT:

• A headshot OR previous work OR request sides, record an audition (please submit by Friday, January 23)

• Subject Line: "[Your Name] - Murder, No Rush"

If you're interested, please feel free to DM me directly here or email AydanMetsch@gmail.com. Script available upon request!

items.text:
**CASTING CALL: PROFESSOR WILLARD**

**Supporting Role | SCAD Senior Thesis Film // *****Opulence***

**March 5-8th, 2026 | Savannah, GA**

**Logline: **

When a Black woman becomes exhausted by passive-aggressive racism at her college, she finds inspiration and connection through a myth of Black angels sent by God.

**Professor Willard (Late 30’s-50’s, White, Male):** 

A public speaking professor at Grove Technical College for five years, originally from a small town in Michigan, now living in the DMV after relocating for his wife, Iyla (African American), who works in D.C. Willard is passionate, articulate, and well-meaning; he teaches with enthusiasm, mentors his students, and doesn’t tolerate disrespect, yet struggles to speak up publicly when racism and microaggressions arise. He privately supports Myra but hesitates within institutional systems. Outside of work, he enjoys quiet nights with his wife, debating over coffee (one sugar), and taking samba classes on Tuesday nights. The role explores the tension between genuine allyship and passive complicity; not a white savior.

**Contact:**

Producer | Hannah Ballard // hballard9hb@gmail.com

Director | Music Miranda // mmiran21@student.scad.edu

*Please submit a headshot and resumé via email for more information. *

*credit & copy of the film comp.

items.text:
🍒 CASTING CALL: University of Westminster Graduation Short Film (LONDON)
CHERRY ON TOP — Black & surreal comedy-drama with surrealist elements

Shooting in London between Feb 14 – March 5 (exact dates TBC) 

5 consecutive shoot days

Cherry on Top is a contained, actor-driven short film exploring emotional decay, morality, denial, and social performance through deadpan absurdity, surrealism, and escalating discomfort.

At a carefully orchestrated dinner party, two couples lose their manners as a wine-fuelled confession of infidelity exposes a far more destabilising secret. 

Throughout the film, a cooked duck on the dinner table slowly rots in plain view, completely ignored by the characters.

Performance style: grounded, restrained, subtext-driven. Think long silences, polite cruelty, sustained social tension.

Catherine (Lead)

Playing age: 30s–40s

The dinner party hostess and Hugh’s wife. Elegant, intelligent, self-righteous, and controlling. Catherine has meticulously curated her life and believes she is emotionally evolved. As the evening unfolds, her composure slowly fractures, revealing unresolved issues and a quietly devious desperation beneath the polish.

A role requiring precision, stillness, restraint, and a slow, unsettling unravel.

Hugh (Supporting)

Playing age: 30s–40s

Catherine’s husband. Timid, gentle, and emotionally reserved, Hugh avoids confrontation and retreats into routine and wine. Deeply likeable and sensitive, he is often overshadowed—until his passivity gives way to something unexpectedly dark.

Played with sincerity and understatement, allowing the absurdity to emerge naturally.

*This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Ingrid. An intimacy coordinator will be present.

Ingrid (LEAD)

Playing age: 30s–40s

Alec’s wife. Obsessive, competitive, and emotionally volatile beneath a polished exterior. Preoccupied with youth, validation, and social hierarchy—especially in comparison to Catherine. Passive-aggressive, smug, and deeply insecure.

Midway through the film, a private bathroom moment exposes her fragility as she spirals alone with her reflection.

A demanding role rooted in desperation masquerading as confidence.

*This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Hugh. An intimacy coordinator will be present.

• This is a non-paid final-year University of Westminster production. Food and transport will be provided. Credit and showreel-quality footage guaranteed. The film may be submitted to festivals.

To apply: 

Please DM or email cherryontop.grad.film@gmail.com with your showreel (if available) and the role(s) you’re applying for.

Open to London-based actors or those able to self-travel.

Feel free to share and thank you! 🍒

🍒 CASTING CALL: University of Westminster Graduation Short Film (LONDON)
CHERRY ON TOP — Black & surreal comedy-drama with surrealist elements

Shooting in London between Feb 14 – March 5 (exact dates TBC) 

5 consecutive shoot days

Cherry on Top is a contained, actor-driven short film exploring emotional decay, morality, denial, and social performance through deadpan absurdity, surrealism, and escalating discomfort.

At a carefully orchestrated dinner party, two couples lose their manners as a wine-fuelled confession of infidelity exposes a far more destabilising secret. 

Throughout the film, a cooked duck on the dinner table slowly rots in plain view, completely ignored by the characters.

Performance style: grounded, restrained, subtext-driven. Think long silences, polite cruelty, sustained social tension.

Catherine (Lead)

Playing age: 30s–40s

The dinner party hostess and Hugh’s wife. Elegant, intelligent, self-righteous, and controlling. Catherine has meticulously curated her life and believes she is emotionally evolved. As the evening unfolds, her composure slowly fractures, revealing unresolved issues and a quietly devious desperation beneath the polish.

A role requiring precision, stillness, restraint, and a slow, unsettling unravel.

Hugh (Supporting)

Playing age: 30s–40s

Catherine’s husband. Timid, gentle, and emotionally reserved, Hugh avoids confrontation and retreats into routine and wine. Deeply likeable and sensitive, he is often overshadowed—until his passivity gives way to something unexpectedly dark.

items.text:
CASTING CALL – PAID LEAD ROLE (SHORT FILM)

Hi everyone!

I’m a film student at the University of Brighton, and I’m currently casting the lead role in my graduation short film, *Interference*.

William Rayner – male, age flexible (playing 45-60)

This is a largely internal role with minimal dialogue. We’re looking for a grounded, naturalistic performance, subtle, lived-in, and emotionally contained rather than theatrical.

The role involves acting opposite a stop-motion character, which will be added in post-production. On set, stand-ins will be used for eyeline and blocking, and performers will be fully supported throughout the process.

PAY & PRACTICALS:

Paid role (£100 per day, 8-hour maximum day with breaks) 

Shoot length: 4–5 days.

Shoot location: Sussex (Hastings & Lewes).

Dates: Late February / early March (flexible based on your schedule within 21 Feb – 29 Mar).

Travel & accommodation fully covered (Airbnb provided).

PRODUCTION INFO:

This is an independent student short film produced as part of my graduation project at the University of Brighton. We plan to submit the finished film to UK and international film festivals.

If this sounds like something you’d be interested in, feel free to send us an email (interferenceshort@gmail.com), comment or DM, and I’ll send over the full casting package with some more information.

Thanks so much!

Elsie Gregory – Writer/Director

items.text:
Hey friends and creatives! 

I wanted to share a quick update—I'm diving back into the world of **live theater, commercials, movies, and modeling gigs,** and I’m super excited to reconnect with this passion!

If you or anyone you know has a project or opportunity where you think I’d be a good fit, **please reach out!** Whether it’s on stage, in front of the camera, or something creative that needs a fresh face, I’d love to collaborate and bring my energy to your team.

Here’s a little about me:

items.text:
Liebe Leute!
Vielen Dank für die ganzen Bewerbungen, wir haben fast den ganzen Cast besetzt.

Nur brauchen wir für unser nächstes Projekt „The Dark-I“  noch eine / einen Make-Up Artist:in.

Projektbeschreibung
Titel: The Dark-I
Genre: Psychologisches Drama / Thriller
Format: Kurzfilm
Logline:
Kyan, ein Junge, der vermeintlich einen Pakt mit dem Teufel geschlossen hat, entpuppt sich nach einem tragischen Vorfall als innerer Kampf zwischen dem „Es“ und dem „Über-Ich“.

📍 Drehort & Zeitraum
• Drehort: Wien
• Drehzeitraum: Februar
• Produktion: No-Budget / Independent

⚠️ Hinweis:
Da es sich um ein No-Budget-Projekt handelt, können wir leider keine Gage anbieten.
👉 Verpflegung am Set ist an jedem Drehtag selbstverständlich vorhanden.
Der Film eignet sich besonders gut für Showreel-Material und Festival-Einreichungen. Der Film wird auch auf YouTube veröffentlicht.

🎥 Anforderungen
• Erfahrung von Vorteil, aber kein Muss
• Zuverlässigkeit & Leidenschaft für Film
• Bereitschaft zur Arbeit an einem Independent-Projekt

📩 Bewerbung
Bitte sendet eure Bewerbung:
• Entweder per PN an mich oder
• Per E-Mail

📧 Kontakt: rahiroproductions@gmail.com

Wir freuen uns auf eure Bewerbungen und darauf, gemeinsam „The Dark-I“ zum Leben zu erwecken. 🎬✨

Dieses Retreat ist kein Urlaub und kein klassisches Coaching.

Es ist ein Raum, in dem du als Schauspieler:in an deiner Wirkung arbeitest –
fernab von Alltag, Ablenkung und Konkurrenzdenken.

Fünf Tage auf Fuerteventura bedeuten Fokus.
Auf dich.
Auf das, was dich vor der Kamera greifbar, interessant und buchbar macht.

Hier geht es nicht um Technik oder „richtig spielen“.
Sondern darum, als Persönlichkeit klarer zu werden,
Präsenz aufzubauen
und dich nicht länger anzupassen, um zu gefallen.

In einer Gruppe von Gleichgesinnten entsteht ein Raum,
in dem du dich zeigen kannst – ohne Maske, ohne Druck.
Genau dort beginnt die Veränderung, die auch im Casting spürbar wird.

🎬 Wenn du mehr erfahren möchtest,
kommentiere „Retreat“
und erhalte den Link zum Essenz-Infocall
🗓 08. Februar | 11:00 Uhr

sharedPost.text:
Call for Entries to the CITTADOR INTERNATIONAL FILM FESTIVAL!

We’re approaching our first deadline of the season, and we’re officially calling on filmmakers from around the world to submit their work to the Cittador International Film Festival (CIFF)!

This year is extra special: Cittador IFF celebrates its 5th anniversary - our first milestone — and we would love to celebrate it together with you and your films.

Cittador IFF is dedicated to showcasing and awarding outstanding independent cinema based solely on artistic quality. Free from commercial constraints, we celebrate films that are bold, original, imaginative, and inspiring - stories that live beyond the mainstream, regardless of genre, background, age, or filmmaking experience.
Our international jury carefully evaluates every submission. Selected and award-winning films receive a public jury statement, highlighting what makes each work unique and meaningful. Award-winning films will be screened in front of an international audience in the famous CineCenter Cinema in Vienna.

We also empower filmmakers to share their voices: selected filmmakers can submit a written interview to be published in the official festival catalog — whether award-winning or not.

Submit now via Filmfreeway, Festhome or TouJiang.

Be part of our journey. Be part of our anniversary.
Submit your film and celebrate independent cinema with CIFF!

https://cittador-iff.com

 #cittadorinternationalfilmfestival #callforentries #filmfestival #cittadoriff

message.text:
Are you an independent filmmaker ready to showcase your work on an international stage? The Cittador International Film Festival (CIFF) in Vienna celebrates inspiration, creativity, and uniqueness in cinema.

Our video “CITTADOR, my CITTADOR! – Winged Words” captures the festival’s spirit and philosophy – highlighting what makes CIFF stand out as a platform for true artistic expression.

Based on the book CITTADOR, my CITTADOR! – Winged Words by Ana Bilic, this video reflects the core values that guide the festival’s film selection: artistic vision, originality, and emotional impact.

Submit your film today and join a global community of storytellers who think differently.

🔗 Learn more & apply: https://iff.cittador.com

#cittadorfilmfestival #indiefilmfest #independentfilm #ciffvienna

🎬TV SERIES PRODUCTION CREW 🎬

We are officially staffing up for the upcoming TV series Between Love & Lust, and we’re looking for passionate, reliable, and creative professionals to join our production team.

OPEN ROLES INCLUDE:
• Camera Operators / Cinematographers
• Audio / Sound Recordists
• Boom Operators
• Production Assistants (PA)
• Lighting Techs
• Grip / Gaffer support

This is a great opportunity to work on a scripted series with strong storytelling, professional direction, and room for growth on future episodes and seasons.

📍 Location: Las Vegas, NV 
Also will be shooting in Los Angeles, Atlanta, and other areas
📆 Start Date:January 30th minimum 5 hours on set for the 30th and 31st
Compensation TBD

If you’re experienced, dependable, and ready to create something special, we want to hear from you.

📩 To Apply:
Send your name, role of interest, experience, and portfolio/reel (if applicable) to: betweenloveandlust@gmail.com 

Let’s make magic ✨🎥

items.text: I am new here and and thought I would introduce myself. I am a filmmaker living on the space coast. Not right now, but I might eventually make a casting call, for a short film. I have my eye of a few film festivals. I have made short films before, but it has been a while since I have worked with people. This also wont include payment. It will be for experience and building resume. I might be a bit rusty so it will also be to re-invoke the skills I retain, get back what I have lost, and learn some new ones. It shall be an experience for the both of us. I do a lot of horror so I will be looking for some young scream queens looking to get their foot in the door,  get some experience, and build their resume.

**CASTING CALL FOR TWITCH LIVE STREAM**

This casting is for talent to appear in a live Twitch stream hosted by well-known streamers. 

**Location: **TBD, Los Angeles, CA

**Pay: **$75/5hours

**Shoot Date: **Friday, 1/30, from 5 PM to 9 PM

**Looking For: **Men of all ages, races, sexualities 

**More Info:** In this Twitch live stream, our hosts will test their GAYDAR by talking with a group of men and trying to guess if they're gay or straight. The goal is to show that gay doesn't have a specific look, so we'd love to see non-stereotypical representations of what both gay and straight can look like! We are seeking men of all ages, races, and sexualities who want to showcase their fun and unique personalities!

**How to Submit:** Fill out the following Google Form

Kinofilmproduktion sucht Production Assistant – Raum Düsseldorf / NRW

Für eine professionelle deutsche Kinofilmproduktion im Low-Budget-Segment (satirische Komödie, ca. 90 Minuten) suchen wir ab sofort einen Production Assistant für Pre-Production und Drehphase bis Mitte September.

Bezahlte Position.

Aufgabenbereich:
Unterstützung der Produktionsleitung in allen organisatorischen Abläufen, Koordination von Vorbereitungsprozessen, Kommunikation mit Crew, Motiven und Dienstleistern sowie Produktionsassistenz während der Dreharbeiten.

Anforderungen:
Strukturierte und selbstständige Arbeitsweise, hohe Verlässlichkeit, Belastbarkeit im Produktionsalltag sowie ausgeprägtes Organisationstalent. Erfahrung im Film- oder Medienbereich von Vorteil.

items.text:
Reminder. Audition Monday coming. 26th. Wanted: 2 actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays.

We are looking for two versatile actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays: “The Balled of Crooked Lane” by Tom Mclennan and “Wake” by Day Sheehan, to be performed on Wed 25th February (the awards evening) at the Gladstone Theatre, Port Sunlight. Both play were part of the Liverpool Fringe and won numerous nominations for best play etc.

Plays and parts descriptions.
“The Ballad of Crooked Lane” is set on the day Edward Rushton, prominent anti-slavery campaigner and blind poet, now well into middle age, awaits eye surgery to regain his sight. While waiting, he goes over his eventful life with his friend and biographer, William Shepherd, the Minister of Gateacre Chapel.

The part: The actor would play Billy the Ballad-monger in one important scene, a lively, upfront character full of humour, a seller of broadside ballads and casual acquaintance of Rushton. The actor would also fulfil several other small roles and be fully active on stage in what is an ensemble production.

“Wake” When Daniel Anderson finds himself in an unfamiliar place with fragments of the previous night missing from his memory, he must piece together the truth of what happened. This experimental drama explores themes of guilt, responsibility, and the price of self-deception in a world where nothing is quite what it seems.

The part: POLICE OFFICER 2 (Any gender, 30s+) - The psychological manipulator who probes emotional wounds. The actor needs to be versatile as this role requires them to be multi faceted

No particular age or even gender is necessarily required We are looking for  actors who can bring the characters to life.

Audition date: Monday 26th January 7pm. Valley Theatre, Childwall Valley Rd, Liverpool L27 3YA

Contact info@valleytheatre.co.uk or turn up on the night. No prep needed. audition will consist of short extract from the script.

Please note: There is no fee for these roles. Hopefully the material and occasion will appeal.

Casting call for a Scouse crime comedy/tragedy short with award winning script
Hoping to shoot in summer 2026, dependent on funding. I’m looking to fill the remaining three roles for the gang of four lads that are essentially the main focus of the film (besides Cookie, the lead role). These are chief supporting roles, and all roles in the film are paid.

No prior acting experience required. If any of the roles leap out at you, I encourage you to go for it. These particular roles definitely need to be scousers - or if you’re that one-in-a-million person who can fake it 😉

I’d prefer if you used the email from the ad below if you want to get in touch, but I’ll still check my inbox on here too anyway.

More roles will be posted soon.

Thanks.

KAGE (Shadow)

Independent Passion Project

Written & Directed by Erfan Shams

📍 Vancouver

🎥 Psychological / Supernatural / Art-house

💰 Modest honorarium + IMDb credit + reel footage

LOGLINE

Mitch, an obsessive feng shui specialist who cleanses homes contaminated by negative energy, discovers an invisible stain while renovating an old house — a stain that awakens a hidden entity each time he tries to erase it.

PRINCIPAL ROLES

MITCH – Male, late 30s–early 40s (Lead)

Controlled, intelligent feng-shui consultant whose need for order turns into obsession.

Requires precision, restraint, strong internal acting.

LILY – Female, late 20s–30s (Co-Lead)

Grounded, observant assistant who witnesses Mitch’s psychological collapse.

Subtle, emotionally intelligent performance.

HOMEOWNER – Female, 60s (Key Supporting)

Quietly powerful, calm, and authoritative. Gatekeeper of the house.

Local Vancouver actors

items.text:
Ogłoszenie aktorskie 🎭🎬

 Statystowanie, Epizody, Role

Dzień dobry! Nazywam się Wiktoria Sułkowska, mam 20, w tym roku 21 lat  (wizualnie wyglądam na nieco młodszą) i z wielką pasją buduję swoje doświadczenie aktorskie. Jestem osobą w miarę  dyspozycyjną, sumienną i niezwykle szybko uczącą się tekstów (oczywiście, jeżeli dostanę je odpowiednio wcześniej, bo raczej nikt nie jest w stanie aż tak szybko nauczyć się tekstu, jak nie otrzyma go wcześniej).

🎥 Moje doświadczenie:

Plan zdjęciowy: Statystowanie w popularnych produkcjach TV: „Na dobre i na złe”, „Barwy szczęścia” oraz epizod i statystowanie jako pielęgniarka w „Na sygnale”, filmach: "Mikołaj Na Sygnale 1" oraz "Uwierz w Mikołaja 2" 🎅🏻, zadawałam również pytanie ~ aktorce i tancerce - Agnieszce Kaczorowskiej na wizji, w programie telewizyjnym "Mówię Wam". 

Scena: Wieloletnie doświadczenie w występach przedszkolnych,  szkolnych i pozaszkolnych (spektakle, apele, przedsięwzięcia artystyczne).

Umiejętności: Bardzo szybko opanowuję scenariusze (często znam tekst całej obsady! przynajmniej tak było, że w branżówce znałam teksty całej obsady i dostawałam zawsze cały scenariusz, w razie zastępowania kogolowiek), co pozwala mi na dużą elastyczność i gotowość do zastępstw w sytuacjach awaryjnych, śpiew, odgrywanie scenek (nawet tych mega emocjonalnych), jazda konna i na łyżwach, znajomość niektórych terminów medycznych, gdyż grałam w serialu "Na Sygnale", w którym w każdym odcinku był jakiś termin medyczny 😁. 

🌟 O mnie:
Aktorstwo to moja pasja od dziecka, którą planuję rozwijać na studiach aktorskich. Jestem osobą pozytywną, komunikatywną i życzliwą (wyróżnioną nagrodą za życzliwość), co przekłada się na świetną współpracę z ekipą na planie.

🤝 Szukam:
Chętnie podejmę się pracy jako:

~ Epizodystka (szczególnie role mówione),

~ Aktorka w rolach głównych w odcinkach lub filmach krótkometrażowych, lub też tych długometrażowych 

~ Statystka w nowych projektach, reklamach i serialach.

Chętnie zagrałabym rolę ratowniczki (to moje marzenie), policjantki, pielęgniarki, itp. 

Jestem gotowa na nowe wyzwania i castingi! Zapraszam do kontaktu w wiadomości prywatnej.

LOKALIZACJA: Warszawa i okolice, Katowice (gdyż mam tylko dwie godziny), okazjonalnie Wrocław.

sharedPost.text:
✋
Za niecały miesiąc mój piąty raz w USA 😊🇺🇸 Jako ciepłolubny wybieram zawsze na odpoczynek dwa stany - Kalifornię i Florydę. Tym razem lecimy się opalać do Miami i pooglądać aligatory 😅🐊 Wyskoczymy też w trakcie naszego ładowania baterii na kilka dni do Nowego Jorku. To będzie długi pobyt na Florydzie i cieszymy się ogromnie 😉 Enjoy! 🌎☀️🌴🐊❤️‍🔥 

https://www.inside.jazzbass.pl

items.text:
Ogłoszenie aktorskie 🎭🎬

 Statystowanie, Epizody, Role

Dzień dobry! Nazywam się Wiktoria Sułkowska, mam 20, w tym roku 21 lat  (wizualnie wyglądam na nieco młodszą) i z wielką pasją buduję swoje doświadczenie aktorskie. Jestem osobą w miarę  dyspozycyjną, sumienną i niezwykle szybko uczącą się tekstów (oczywiście, jeżeli dostanę je odpowiednio wcześniej, bo raczej nikt nie jest w stanie aż tak szybko nauczyć się tekstu, jak nie otrzyma go wcześniej).

🎥 Moje doświadczenie:

Plan zdjęciowy: Statystowanie w popularnych produkcjach TV: „Na dobre i na złe”, „Barwy szczęścia” oraz epizod i statystowanie jako pielęgniarka w „Na sygnale”, filmach: "Mikołaj Na Sygnale 1" oraz "Uwierz w Mikołaja 2" 🎅🏻, zadawałam również pytanie ~ aktorce i tancerce - Agnieszce Kaczorowskiej na wizji, w programie telewizyjnym "Mówię Wam". 

Scena: Wieloletnie doświadczenie w występach przedszkolnych,  szkolnych i pozaszkolnych (spektakle, apele, przedsięwzięcia artystyczne).

Umiejętności: Bardzo szybko opanowuję scenariusze (często znam tekst całej obsady! przynajmniej tak było, że w branżówce znałam teksty całej obsady i dostawałam zawsze cały scenariusz, w razie zastępowania kogolowiek), co pozwala mi na dużą elastyczność i gotowość do zastępstw w sytuacjach awaryjnych, śpiew, odgrywanie scenek (nawet tych mega emocjonalnych), jazda konna i na łyżwach, znajomość niektórych terminów medycznych, gdyż grałam w serialu "Na Sygnale", w którym w każdym odcinku był jakiś termin medyczny 😁. 

🌟 O mnie:
Aktorstwo to moja pasja od dziecka, którą planuję rozwijać na studiach aktorskich. Jestem osobą pozytywną, komunikatywną i życzliwą (wyróżnioną nagrodą za życzliwość), co przekłada się na świetną współpracę z ekipą na planie.

🤝 Szukam:
Chętnie podejmę się pracy jako:

~ Epizodystka (szczególnie role mówione),

~ Aktorka w rolach głównych w odcinkach lub filmach krótkometrażowych, lub też tych długometrażowych 

~ Statystka w nowych projektach, reklamach i serialach.

Chętnie zagrałabym rolę ratowniczki (to moje marzenie), policjantki, pielęgniarki, itp. 

Jestem gotowa na nowe wyzwania i castingi! Zapraszam do kontaktu w wiadomości prywatnej.

LOKALIZACJA: Warszawa i okolice, Katowice (gdyż mam tylko dwie godziny), okazjonalnie Wrocław.

items.text:
Szukacie prezentu, który wywoła efekt WOW i nie wyląduje w szufladzie? 

Cześć! Chciałem Wam pokazać coś, co ostatnio dopracowałem. To personalizowane obrazy na płótnie, ale w wydaniu AI. Możecie zamienić zdjęcie bliskiej osoby, psa albo kota w postać z komiksu, superbohatera, czy – jak w przypadku mojej babci na zdjęciu – w raperkę w dresie! 

Najfajniejsze jest to, że nie kupujecie kota w worku:

Wchodzicie na jakchceszsklep.pl

Wgrywacie zdjęcie.

Opisujecie pomysł (np. "zrób z niego wikinga" albo "ubierz ją w dres").

AI wygeneruje Wam podgląd ZA DARMO!  Możecie się pobawić i zobaczyć efekty bez żadnych opłat.

Jeśli efekt Wam się spodoba, drukujemy to na porządnym płótnie. 

 Sprawdźcie sami: jakchceszsklep.pl
 Z kodem PREZENT10 macie -10% na całe zamówienie.

Kogo z Waszych znajomych wysłalibyście na taką metamorfozę? Dajcie znać w komentarzach!

[](http://jakchceszsklep.pl/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExYkJFMW1GNGozVzJyRDI3NXNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR7fY1b-c0bv_KWyuQUszgaUFILQi6_njG7L1j_VRgpZP42kQCvfCLvxDYP0Cg_aem_wvmcs70ayXSWNSv86P-pLA)

items.text:
Open casting Łódź
Jestem studentką na Uniwersytecie Łódzkim i w ramach projektu dyplomowego organizuję pokaz mody młodych projektantów. Pokaz ten ma się odbyć 23.05.2026 roku w Klubokawiarni Willa w Parku Poniatowskiego w Łodzi. Pokaz będzie zbiorowy, do współpracy zaprosiłam 7 projektantów.

Szukam modelek i modeli chętnych do wsparcia naszej inicjatywy. Nie musisz się przejmować jeśli nie masz doświadczenia, szukam przede wszystkim nieprofesjonalnych lub półprofesjonalnych modeli i modelek. 

Wymagania: nie mam praktycznie żadnych. Każdy może się zgłosić!

Wiek: 16+ (ze zgodą rodzica)

Zgłoszenia zbieramy do 15.02.2026

https://forms.gle/x35KUgw3h4rx6Pc97 ( link do formularzu zgłoszeniowego)

items.text:
**WARSZAWA 3 i 4 lutego**

**film fabularny**

**Stawka: 410-450 zł za 2 dni płatne gotówką po planie drugiego dnia**

 

Do nowego biograficznego filmu fabularnego osadzonego w latach 70tych szukam Statystów głównie mężczyzn, ale jest też miejsce dla kilku kobiet.

 

Ze względu na obiekt, w którym gramy szukamy osób TYLKO Z OBYWATELSTWEM POLSKIM.

 

Zdjęcia kontynuacyjne 3 i 4 lutego więc wymagana jest dyspozycyjność w oba dni.

 

Strzyżenie dla panów: 30 stycznia lub 2 lutego **(dodatkowo płatne 90 zł)**

Panie pokazują się jedynie w charakteryzacji – dni jak powyżej **(dodatkowo płatne 50 zł)**

Miejsce i godziny jeszcze do ustalenia.

 

**Stawka: 180 zł /dzień zdjęciowy + próby charakteryzacji**

** **

**Wytyczne charakteryzacji:**

**MĘŻCZYŹNI:**

- WŁOSY- raczej dłuższe, nachodzące na uszy i kark. Nieakceptowane są włosy obcięte bardzo krótko maszynką ,wygolone boki i kark z dłuższą górą, wycięte wzorki na włosach oraz nienaturalne kolory oraz farbowane np. na czarny.

- ZAROST - mogą być wąsy ,baki, lub pełny zarost ale naturalny niestylizowany u barbera.

- panowie na mundurowych mogą mieć włosy krótsze, odsłonięte uszy i kark, ale niewygoleni maszynką. Ogoleni na gładko.

**Kogo szukamy?**

- PRACOWNICY CYWILNI – głównie mężczyźni w wieku ok. 25-55 lat. Tutaj właśnie kilka kobiet w tym samym wieku.

- STRAŻNICY W MUNDURACH – mężczyźni w wieku 18-25 lat

 

Zgłoszenia poproszę na adres: **ewelina.wika@podtytulem.pl**

W tytule: **K23**

W treści: imię i nazwisko, wiek, nr telefonu, miejscowość + wymiary: wzrost, klatka, pas, biodra, rozmiar ubrania i buta

W załączniku: **ZDJĘCIE TWARZY I SYLWETKI: tylko z dnia zgłoszenia + panowie zdjęcie z profilu**

** **

**ZDJĘCIE TWARZY** - portretowe selfie w dziennym świetle, na wprost, patrząc w obiektyw. Bez żadnych filtrów. Bez okularów. Bez nakrycia głowy. Kolorowe.

**ZDJĘCIE SYLWETKI** – aktualne, cała sylwetka
